Subject: RE: [VB] Oversized crank pulley ?'s

Several of the books, including the current VW interchange manual state that
there is an air stall at certain RPM's above factory maximum, (I have no
idea what that rpm is) because the air volume cannot pass by the cylinders
quick enough. There was also mention of the sheet metal fans flying apart at
hi rpm.

67 Single Cab, DP 1641cc 34PICT
71 Trike 1776cc 32/36 Progressive
VolksAir 1585cc 28 PICT
